definition: to land/to come ashore/to make landfall (of typhoon etc)/to log in (frequently used erroneous variant of 登錄|登录[deng1 lu4])

to scale (a height)/to ascend/to mount/to publish or record/to enter (e.g. in a register)/to press down with the foot/to step or tread on/to put on (shoes or trousers) (dialect)/to be gathered and taken to the threshing ground (old)
moon landing/to land on the moon

sentences.english: He also created a functioning replica of MySpace's log-in page.
sentences.chinese: 斯克姆還創建了MySpace的登陸網頁的複製品。

sentences.english: Enable logons to the data store server.
sentences.chinese: 啓用登陸到數據存儲服務器。
士兵離開運輸航登陸了。

sentences.english: The landings called for an assault on a five-divisional front.
sentences.chinese: 登陸要求在五條分割的戰線上進行突擊。

sentences.english: The landing on moon heralds a new era of space.
sentences.chinese: 翻譯月球登陸預示着航空史上又一個新時代的到來。

sentences.english: He landed with a guard of 500 men to sign the treaty.
sentences.chinese: 他偕同500人的警衛隊一起登陸，簽訂條約。

sentences.english: As a matter of fact, extraterrestrials have landed.
sentences.chinese: 事實上，外星人登陸過地球。

sentences.english: How do I log on the company's intranet?
sentences.chinese: 我要如何登陸公司的辦公網？

sentences.english: Hello, please login now to re-try the game.
sentences.chinese: 您好，請您現在重新登陸游戲。

sentences.english: They were coming in to land on the north coast of Crete .
sentences.chinese: 他們將從克里特島北海岸登陸上島。

sentences.english: Our mission is to harass the landing of the main japanese expeditionary force .
sentences.chinese: 我們的任務是騷亂日本遠征軍主力的登陸。

sentences.english: If aliens landed here right now, what would you do?
sentences.chinese: 如果此刻有外星人在此登陸，你會怎麼做？

sentences.english: The beach defences were softened up before the landing craft was in.
sentences.chinese: 在登陸艇駛入以前，海灘防禦工事已遭削弱。

sentences.english: While the link-sharing part of the service doesn't require a login, the bookmarking function does require users to register accounts.
sentences.chinese: 網址分享服務無需登陸，而書籤功能則需要註冊。

sentences.english: New sound when logging into pvp. net.
sentences.chinese: 新的登陸賬號時開門聲音。

sentences.english: When fascism comes to America, it will come wrapped in an America flag.
sentences.chinese: ‘法西斯主義登陸美國時，總會包着一面美國旗。’

definition: to go online/to put sth online
to rush (to do sth urgent)/to try to be the first/to forestall
to go online/to connect to the Internet/(of a document etc) to be uploaded to the Internet/(tennis, volleyball etc) to move in close to the net
official website (abbr. for 官方網站|官方网站[guan1 fang1 wang3 zhan4])
to enter and garrison/(fig.) to establish a presence in
to open up (windows for air, ideas for discussion, transportation routes etc)
to bloom/to open/to be open (to the public)/to open up (to the outside)/to be open-minded/unrestrained by convention/unconstrained in one's sexuality
